Twitter is abuzz after University of Limpopo students were seen standing up at their desks and protesting against an exam paper that was "too difficult". The education students were writing a philosophy paper, which they said was too hard. Capricorn FM reported: "The University of Limpopo has confirmed that students have refused to write a scheduled Educational Philosophy test at the campus in Mankweng on Tuesday." The station went on to say: "Acting spokesperson for the university Johannes Selepe says a full report of what transpired will be released tomorrow."